<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1"/>
        <title>
            @product.name@ v@product.version@ - Issue Tracking
        </title>
        <link href="css/bps-docs.css" rel="stylesheet"/>
        <link href="styles/dist-docs.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" media="all"/>
    </head>
    <body xml:lang="en">
        <h1>
            WSO2 Business Process Server (BPS) Issue Tracking
        </h1>

        <p>
            @product.name@ is developed on top of the revolutionary WSO2 Carbon platform. To get an overall
            idea on the issue management of the @product.name@, you might need to have a look at the
            Carbon platform issue tracking as well.
        </p>
        <h2>Overview</h2>

        <p>This project uses
        <a class="externalLink" href="http://www.atlassian.com/software/jira">Jira</a> a J2EE-based,
        issue tracking and project management application.</p>

        <h2>Issue Tracking of the BPS Product</h2>
        <p>Issues, bugs, and feature requests for the <a href="http://wso2.org/projects/bps">
            @product.name@ product</a> should be submitted to the
            following issue tracking system.</p>
        <div class="source">
            <a class="externalLink" href="http://wso2.org/jira/browse/BPS">http://wso2.org/jira/browse/BPS</a>
        </div>
        <h2>Issue Tracking of the Carbon Platform</h2>
        <p>Issues, bugs, and feature requests for the <a href="http://wso2.org/projects/carbon">
            WSO2 Carbon platform</a> should be submitted to the following issue tracking system.</p>
        <div class="source">
            <a class="externalLink" href="http://wso2.org/jira/browse/CARBON">http://wso2.org/jira/browse/CARBON</a>
        </div>

    </body>
</html>
